# Debugger — rag

## Investigation sequence

1. Check the ingestion log for the last run — where did it stop?
2. Verify embedding model match: `EMBEDDING_MODEL` in `rag/.env` must equal `EMBEDDING_MODEL` in `chain/.env`
3. Check Qdrant collection status using the evaluator MCP tool
4. Verify the vector dimension in the collection matches `EMBEDDING_DIMENSION`
5. Check for partial ingestion (some movies missing) vs. failed ingestion (collection empty)

## Key files

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `src/rag/ingest.py` | Main ingestion script |
| `src/rag/embedder.py` | OpenAI embedding calls |
| `src/rag/qdrant_client.py` | Qdrant write operations |
| `.env` / `.env.example` | Collection name, model, API keys |

## Common failure patterns

| Symptom | Likely cause |
|---------|-------------|
| 0 results from semantic search in chain | Embedding model mismatch between rag and chain |
| Ingestion stops mid-run | OpenAI rate limit (429) — check retry logic |
| Qdrant 400 on upsert | Vector dimension mismatch — check `EMBEDDING_DIMENSION` |
| `sys.exit(1)` in logs | Issue #6 — QdrantVectorStore library code — note in report |

## Anti-Focus

Do NOT fix the code. Produce a defect report. Leave fixes to Developer.
